{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4539048c-b7fd-4afd-bf3a-73ba7963faf5","content":"Here's the recommended setup:\n\n## 1. Project file (`YourTests.csproj`)\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8\">\n\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n\n</Project>\n```\n\nThat's it — `MSTest.Sdk` bundles MSTest, the runner, and code coverage. No extra NuGet references needed.\n\n## 2. Enable parallel execution\n\nAdd an assembly-level attribute (e.g., in a `Usings.cs` or `AssemblyInfo.cs`):\n\n```csharp\n[assembly: Parallelize(Scope = ExecutionScope.MethodLevel)]\n```\n\nThis runs all test methods in parallel across classes.\n\n## 3. Make database tests sequential\n\nMark your database test class with `[DoNotParallelize]`:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\n[DoNotParallelize]\npublic class DatabaseIntegrationTests\n{\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task Can_Insert_Record() { /* ... */ }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task Can_Read_After_Write() { /* ... */ }\n}\n```\n\n## Summary\n\n| Concern | Mechanism |\n|---------|-----------|\n| Minimal project | `MSTest.Sdk` (replaces 3+ packages) |\n| Parallel by default | `[assembly: Parallelize]` |\n| Sequential DB tests | `[DoNotParallelize]` on the class |\n\n`DoNotParallelize` ensures that class's tests run alone — no other tests execute concurrently with them, preventing database state conflicts.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9c0c6ee6-5395-4fda-93f1-ba6cd7598693","outputTokens":399,"requestId":"E445:3A3321:1C112E5:1E11674:6A02FC1D"},"id":"61746cb5-df46-44af-abfb-08d09eae24bb","timestamp":"2026-05-12T10:08:44.518Z","parentId":"6aed7cf1-1d71-4bbe-ab8a-7921083dbabc"}
